<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1144000' id='t-1144000'>then using a little bit of the electricity control that process,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1148000' id='t-1148000'>and for 450 watts, which is a little more than half of its waste heat,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1154000' id='t-1154000'>it will make 10 gallons an hour of distilled water</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1156000' id='t-1156000'>from anything that comes into it to cool it.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1158000' id='t-1158000'>So if we put this box on here in a few years,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1161000' id='t-1161000'>could we have a solution to transportation, electricity,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1167000' id='t-1167000'>and communication, and maybe drinkable water</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1171000' id='t-1171000'>in a sustainable package that weighs 60 pounds?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1175000' id='t-1175000'>I don't know, but we'll try it.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1177000' id='t-1177000'>I better shut up.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1179000' id='t-1179000'>(Applause)</span>
</span>
